description: Returns details of the service updates.

parameters.name: ClusterNames
parameters.description: The list of cluster names to identify service updates to apply. (string) ---

parameters.name: Status
parameters.description: The status(es) of the service updates to filter on. (string) ---

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: An optional argument to pass in case the total number of records exceeds the value of MaxResults. If nextToken is returned, there are more results available. The value of nextToken is a unique pagination token for each page. Make the call again using the returned token to retrieve the next page. Keep all other arguments unchanged.

nested_items.name: ClusterName
nested_items.description: The name of the cluster to which the service update applies.

nested_items.name: ServiceUpdateName
nested_items.description: The unique ID of the service update.

nested_items.name: ReleaseDate
nested_items.description: The date when the service update is initially available.

nested_items.name: Description
nested_items.description: Provides details of the service update.

nested_items.name: Status
nested_items.description: The status of the service update.

nested_items.name: Type
nested_items.description: Reflects the nature of the service update.

nested_items.name: Engine
nested_items.description: The name of the engine for which a service update is available.

nested_items.name: NodesUpdated
nested_items.description: A list of nodes updated by the service update.

nested_items.name: AutoUpdateStartDate
nested_items.description: The date at which the service update will be automatically applied.
